The term the "unsaturation" used in this specification points out condensed ring of the formula I by which the valence of each atom of condensed ring is not satisfy|filled with hydrogen or another substituent.
For example, the double bond of the carbon atom which adjoins in condensed ring can mutually be carried out.
The unsaturation can include deleting a pair of following at least 1 and making the valence of a carbocyclic-ring atom perfect by a double bond at least by these deletion;
